rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship type that is used to relate an element of the Satori ontology to a concept in an external source with a qualifier about how the element and the concept are related, i.e. "equivalent", "narrower" or "broader" in meaning.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related External Concept

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An element in the external controlled vocabulary that is related to the given object of the Satori Ontology.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Concept

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The element of the Satori Ontology, viz. an entity, type or property, that is related to a concept in an external controlled vocabulary.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A qualifier that indicates how the Satori Ontology element and the concept from the external controlled vocabulary are related, i.e. "equivalent", "narrower" or "broader" in meaning.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The name of the external controlled vocabulary that includes the concept that is related to the Satori Ontology object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Source

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the semantic relation data between Satori entities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Internal Concepts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that is used to specify an informal relation between the subject and object. This property can be used for data source attributes whose semantics are somewhat opaque but which need to be aligned with the Satori Ontology for whatever reason. For example, a data source might have an attribute indicating the "top recruiter" for a given educational institution. Even though it's not entirely clear what is meant by "top recruiter" here, we might want to merge this information with Satori, and the property mso:common.related_internal_concept.informal_relation provides a way to do this.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Informal Relation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:common.related_internal_concept to the object mso:type.object of the semantic relationship. For example, in the semantic relationship 'Mammal is a broader term of cat', the common.related_internal_concept.object_object is 'cat'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:common.related_external_concept to its part of speech, mso:language.part_of_speech.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Part of Speech
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: This property is relevant to common.related_external_concept, but not to common.related_internal_concept. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:common.related_internal_concept to the semantic relation between the subject Satori object and the object Satori object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Semantic Relation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property whose value is the degree of similarity (a number between 0 and 1) between the corresponding values of common.related_internal_concept.subject_object and common.related_internal_concept.object_object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Similarity Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:common.related_internal_concept to the source of the semantic relation data. This is not necessarily the same as context, since Freebase, for example, contains a good deal of semantic information for objects whose source is WordNet. Note that this property is needed, because the type mso:common.related_internal_concept can be used to collect information about how a source semantically structures Satori entities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Source

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:common.related_internal_concept to the subject mso:type.object of the semantic relationship. For example, in the semantic relationship 'Mammal is a broader term of cat', the common.related_internal_concept.subject_object value is 'Mammal'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains properties whose expected types have been relaxed from whatever they are in MSO to mso:common.text. The purpose of this type is to facilitate ingestion of data that uses standard attributes but nonstandard values.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relaxed Property

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains texts that purport to describe real past events.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Report

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a report to the date when the event described in the report is alleged to have occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the report has been confirmed or disconfirmed. If the report has been confirmed, the flag is set to 0. If the report has been disconfirmed, the flag is set to 1. Otherwise, the flag is not set.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: False

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a report to the value that is ascribed by the report. Note that the property mso:common.report.object should be populated only if mso:common.report.property is also populated
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a report to the property in the ontology, e.g. mso:people.deceased_person.date_of_death, that is the focus of the report.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Property

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type containing standard qualifiers that indicate how two elements from a taxonomy or controlled vocabulary are related, e.g. "equivalent", "narrower" or "broader" in meaning.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Semantic Relation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration value that indicates that the Satori Ontology element is broader in meaning than the concept from the external controlled vocabulary.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Broader

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the semantic concept of category. Category is a broader concept than mso:common.semantic_relation.instance. Works may be categorized by subject, for example, and not be an instance of the subject.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the sematic relation that relates what is required to be done before the first can be done. For example, 'to sleep' is entailed by 'to snore'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Entails

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration value that indicates that the Satori Ontology element and the concept from the external controlled vocabulary are equivalent in meaning.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Equivalent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the sematic relation that relates an instance to a type. For example, '9/11' is an instance of 'terrorist attack'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Instance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the semantic relation of meronym that is specific to membership. Use common.semantic_relation.meronym when the meronym relationship is unspecified.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Member Meronym

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the sematic relation that relates a part to a whole. For example, 'finger' is a meronym of 'hand', since fingers are a part of hands.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Meronym

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration value that indicates that the Satori Ontology element is narrower in meaning than the concept from the external controlled vocabulary.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Narrower
